02:01.455 --> 02:03.224
What is my phone number?

02:03.257 --> 02:04.692
- I know your phone number.
Want me to tell you?

02:04.725 --> 02:06.260
- No, don't.

02:06.294 --> 02:08.196
I want to see how long
it takes me to remember.

02:08.229 --> 02:09.697
Do I have Alzheimer's?

02:09.730 --> 02:12.266
- No. Remember at the movies,
when I couldn't remember

02:12.300 --> 02:14.202
what's-her-face's name,
with the hair?

02:14.235 --> 02:15.336
From that show we used to love?

02:15.369 --> 02:17.205
- Oh, yeah.
I love her.

02:17.238 --> 02:18.272
What's her name again?

02:18.306 --> 02:19.440
- I have no idea.

02:19.473 --> 02:21.309
But you keep changing
the subject.

02:21.342 --> 02:23.444
- From what?
I can't remember.

02:23.477 --> 02:24.578
- Graham.

02:24.612 --> 02:26.547
- Oh, yeah.
It's fine.

02:26.580 --> 02:29.617
We kissed for a second, and then
I came back to my senses,

02:29.650 --> 02:31.118
and now he's staying
with a cousin.

02:31.219 --> 02:32.386
- Okay, good riddance.

02:32.420 --> 02:33.654
See ya never, Graham.

02:33.687 --> 02:35.389
Sorry I'm talking
like Cindy Brady.

02:35.423 --> 02:36.724
I just put in a new Invisalign.

02:36.757 --> 02:38.392
- Oh, I couldn't tell.

02:38.426 --> 02:40.794
I forgot you and Hazel
are doing that whole

02:40.828 --> 02:42.363
mother-daughter
teeth straightening thing.

02:42.396 --> 02:43.664
You guys are so cute.

02:43.697 --> 02:45.333
- Yeah, well, when your
ten-year-old tells you

02:45.366 --> 02:47.134
that you have
"granny teeth,"

02:47.235 --> 02:48.236
you have to take action.

02:48.236 --> 02:49.570
- What is wrong with us?

02:49.603 --> 02:51.239
Everyone's always saying things

02:51.239 --> 02:52.873
like, "60 is the new 40."

02:52.906 --> 02:54.242
- Oh, no.
That's bullshit.

02:54.275 --> 02:55.609
40 is the new 70.

02:55.643 --> 02:57.611
- 70?
Okay, you wish.

02:57.645 --> 02:59.613
- Ooh, I like that bag.

02:59.647 --> 03:01.482
- Yeah, I think
it's a Von Weber.

03:01.515 --> 03:02.716
- Oh, my God.

03:02.750 --> 03:04.685
That's one of Brooke's bags?

03:04.718 --> 03:05.919
- [stammers]

03:05.953 --> 03:08.155
Sorry.
- That's not funny.

03:08.256 --> 03:10.258
I just liked something
that Brooke designed.

03:10.291 --> 03:11.725
It was like a blind
taste test

03:11.759 --> 03:12.726
that I failed.

03:12.760 --> 03:13.827
- It's a cute bag.

03:13.861 --> 03:15.663
Don't be so hard on yourself.

03:15.696 --> 03:18.266
- No, if she's designing
something that's actually good,

03:18.266 --> 03:19.400
I can't make fun of her.

03:19.433 --> 03:20.734
Her career is en fuego,

03:20.768 --> 03:23.904
and I'm shooting
doorman head shots for free.

03:23.937 --> 03:26.607
- No, you just need
to work on your hustle.

03:26.640 --> 03:28.776
Have you ever
pitched yourself to Brooke?

03:28.809 --> 03:30.444
- Ugh, no.

03:30.478 --> 03:33.347
First of all, you can't mix
work and family.

03:33.381 --> 03:35.283
That's inevitable disaster,

03:35.316 --> 03:36.684
and second, she knows what I do.

03:36.717 --> 03:38.586
She could've hired me
if she wanted to.

03:38.619 --> 03:40.554
- Well, you don't ask,
you don't get.

03:40.588 --> 03:41.555
You're 82.

03:41.589 --> 03:42.556
What are you gonna do,

03:42.590 --> 03:43.557
wait until you're 90

03:43.591 --> 03:44.725
to get your career in gear?

03:44.758 --> 03:45.726
- Ow.

03:45.759 --> 03:48.195
Elder abuse.

03:48.296 --> 03:50.197
- That was delicious, guys.
Thanks again.

03:50.298 --> 03:51.465
- Hello, Anderson.

03:51.499 --> 03:52.866
- Hey, what are you doing here?

03:52.900 --> 03:54.502
- Hi.

03:54.535 --> 03:57.471
I'm meeting Celia
for our standing lunch date.

03:57.505 --> 03:59.440
And who have we here?

03:59.473 --> 04:01.675
- These are the wunderkinds
I was telling you about:

04:01.709 --> 04:03.611
Chad and Omar,
from my new job.

04:03.644 --> 04:05.546
- Yes.
Charmed, I'm sure.

04:05.579 --> 04:07.615
Is the rest of the company
this handsome?

04:07.648 --> 04:09.417
- [laughs]
This is my mother,

04:09.450 --> 04:10.418
Mrs. von Weber.

04:10.451 --> 04:12.486
- Oh, so we have you to thank

04:12.520 --> 04:13.754
for bringing Andy
into the world.

04:13.787 --> 04:15.323
[both laugh]

04:15.356 --> 04:16.824
- Anderson, may I have a word?

04:16.857 --> 04:18.626
- Sure, I'll see you guys
back at the office.

04:18.659 --> 04:19.927
- Nice meeting you.

04:19.960 --> 04:21.929
- Yes.

04:21.962 --> 04:22.996
How dare you embarrass me
that way?

04:23.030 --> 04:24.498
- What?
What did I say?

04:24.532 --> 04:26.400
- You know goddamn well
what you said.

04:26.434 --> 04:29.337
You introduced me
as your mother.

04:29.337 --> 04:30.771
- Are you not my mother?

04:30.804 --> 04:32.906
- Must I spell everything out
for you?

04:32.940 --> 04:35.008
You are a middle-aged man now,

04:35.042 --> 04:37.511
so think about how that
impacts me.

04:37.545 --> 04:38.546
- You?

04:38.579 --> 04:40.348
- Yes.

04:40.348 --> 04:42.516
You are so self-involved.

04:42.550 --> 04:44.552
Until further notice,

04:44.585 --> 04:46.754
I would prefer
that you introduce me

04:46.787 --> 04:48.722
as your dear friend.

04:48.756 --> 04:51.825
- Your table is ready,
Mrs. von Weber.

04:51.859 --> 04:56.430
*

04:56.464 --> 05:00.401
- So, wow, this is
like a real wedding dress.

05:00.434 --> 05:01.669
- But do you think
it's solemn enough

05:01.702 --> 05:02.670
for the occasion?

05:02.703 --> 05:03.904
- Well, I mean, given that

05:03.937 --> 05:05.439
it's just a vows renewal, I--

05:05.473 --> 05:07.408
- "Just a vows renewal?"

05:07.441 --> 05:09.577
- Jill, this is much
more meaningful

05:09.610 --> 05:10.711
than a wedding.

05:10.744 --> 05:12.446
Lex and I have been
to darker places

05:12.480 --> 05:14.548
than you could
ever understand.

05:16.817 --> 05:17.885
- Anyway.

05:17.918 --> 05:19.019
Shifting gears,

05:19.052 --> 05:21.789
I just wanted to remind you

05:21.822 --> 05:23.757
that I'm still pluggin' away

05:23.791 --> 05:27.027
at ye old photography biz,

05:27.060 --> 05:29.730
just in case, you know,

05:29.763 --> 05:32.600
you...

05:32.633 --> 05:34.535
- Yes?

05:34.568 --> 05:36.904
- Well, I mean, no pressure,
but if you ever need

05:36.937 --> 05:40.040
a photographer for anything...

05:40.073 --> 05:42.610
- Oh, you're asking me
for a job.

05:42.643 --> 05:44.812
Jill, I say this with love.

05:44.845 --> 05:47.915
I believe mixing
work and family

05:47.948 --> 05:50.818
is never wise.

05:50.851 --> 05:52.620
- Yeah, I have heard that said.

05:52.653 --> 05:53.621
Sorry.

05:53.654 --> 05:54.788
- Don't be sorry.

05:54.822 --> 05:56.624
I just know so much more now,

05:56.657 --> 05:59.059
