10:03.904 --> 10:05.238
Detail.

10:05.272 --> 10:07.708
- Is--is this okay?

10:07.741 --> 10:10.844
This is what you meant
by "arty," right?

10:10.878 --> 10:12.045
- Uh, sure.

10:12.079 --> 10:14.848
*

10:14.882 --> 10:16.784
- [humming]

10:16.817 --> 10:18.251
- Hi, is there anything

10:18.285 --> 10:19.619
I can help you with today?

10:19.653 --> 10:21.054
- Yes, I was hoping
you could help me

10:21.088 --> 10:23.290
with some anti-aging products.

10:23.323 --> 10:24.825
Moisturizers, lotions,

10:24.858 --> 10:26.894
anything that promotes
springy skin.

10:26.927 --> 10:28.361
You know, shrinks pores,

10:28.395 --> 10:29.930
erases broken blood vessels.

10:29.963 --> 10:30.998
- Certainly.

10:31.031 --> 10:32.065
If you'd like to sit down,

10:32.099 --> 10:33.133
I'd be happy to give you

10:33.166 --> 10:35.068
a personal consultation.

10:35.102 --> 10:36.937
- I beg your pardon.

10:36.970 --> 10:38.638
My face is as soft

10:38.672 --> 10:40.273
as the inner thigh of a newborn.

10:40.307 --> 10:42.175
It's my son that needs help.

10:42.209 --> 10:43.343
He's approaching middle age

10:43.376 --> 10:45.178
with no vanity, fear,

10:45.212 --> 10:47.614
or regard for how it affects
the rest of us.

10:47.647 --> 10:48.916
- Believe it or not,

10:48.949 --> 10:50.383
I see a lot of this.

10:51.952 --> 10:55.122
- I find that
strangely comforting.

10:55.155 --> 10:56.123
- Terrific.

10:56.156 --> 10:57.590
Smile, George.

10:57.624 --> 11:00.560
Work it.
W-E-R-Q.

11:00.728 --> 11:02.295
Flash those baby blues.

11:02.329 --> 11:04.164
And great.

11:04.197 --> 11:05.733
Head shot, three-quarter,

11:05.733 --> 11:07.000
profile.

11:07.034 --> 11:08.836
That's a wrap, George.

11:08.869 --> 11:11.371
- [stammering]
Oh, is that it?

11:11.404 --> 11:12.906
'Cause I heard you asked Carlton

11:12.940 --> 11:15.743
to do all kinds
of different shots.

11:16.944 --> 11:17.945
- I'm sorry, what?

11:17.978 --> 11:19.279
- Yeah.

11:19.312 --> 11:22.750
What's he got
that I don't?

11:22.750 --> 11:24.084
- Terrific, George.

11:24.117 --> 11:26.019
Yes, awesome, George.

11:26.053 --> 11:27.020
Secret!

11:27.054 --> 11:28.255
Ooh.

11:28.288 --> 11:29.356
Yes, Michael.

11:29.389 --> 11:31.759
Hello, bellman.
Dingdong.

11:31.792 --> 11:33.126
Fragile.

11:33.160 --> 11:34.127
Love those epaulets.

11:34.161 --> 11:35.362
Give me the other epaulet.

11:35.395 --> 11:37.030
And salute.

11:37.064 --> 11:38.031
All right, Abe.

11:38.065 --> 11:39.432
What's in the luggage?

11:39.466 --> 11:41.034
Blow that whistle.
Taxi!

11:41.068 --> 11:42.803
It's gonna be a bumpy ride.

11:42.836 --> 11:44.071
There's my bags.

11:44.104 --> 11:45.238
Make love to that lens.

11:45.272 --> 11:46.373
Give it to me, Mark.

11:46.406 --> 11:47.374
Yes.

11:47.407 --> 11:48.776
Work it.

11:48.809 --> 11:51.779
[jazzy music]

11:51.779 --> 11:54.782
[people conversing quietly]

11:56.950 --> 11:59.987
[rock music]

12:00.020 --> 12:01.321
- You know, not to brag,

12:01.354 --> 12:03.924
but these doorman photos
are really good.

12:03.957 --> 12:05.058
- That's great, honey.

12:05.092 --> 12:06.359
Can I take this thing off now?

12:06.393 --> 12:07.360
- No, your mother said--

12:07.394 --> 12:08.361
- Ah!

12:08.395 --> 12:09.863
"Dear friend."

12:09.897 --> 12:11.799
- [laughs]
Your "dear friend"

12:11.799 --> 12:13.366
said that you have to wear
Georgia Louise

12:13.400 --> 12:15.368
for 20 minutes every day

12:15.402 --> 12:16.970
if you want to look
like an embryo.

12:17.004 --> 12:20.007
[phone chiming]

12:21.341 --> 12:23.476
Did Lex mention
why they're so hell-bent

12:23.510 --> 12:25.946
on taking us to dinner tonight?
- Nope.

12:25.979 --> 12:26.980
- I bet you Brooke just wants

12:27.014 --> 12:28.015
to finish lecturing me

12:28.048 --> 12:29.817
on how to be a career gal.

12:29.850 --> 12:32.419
- And just because they're
on their second honeymoon,

12:32.452 --> 12:34.721
why do we have to eat dinner
in the middle of the night?

12:34.822 --> 12:35.823
This isn't Barthelona.

12:35.856 --> 12:37.124
- It's 9:45.

12:37.157 --> 12:38.826
It's not the middle
of the night.

12:38.826 --> 12:40.060
Let's get going.
- [grunts]

12:41.929 --> 12:44.031
[groans]

12:44.064 --> 12:46.033
- Oh, babe, no.

12:46.066 --> 12:47.134
Those jeans.

12:47.167 --> 12:48.368
- What, no jeans at this place?

12:48.401 --> 12:50.337
- Well, maybe jeans
at this place,

12:50.370 --> 12:52.072
but not dad jeans.

12:52.105 --> 12:54.174
You look like
a high school math teacher

12:54.207 --> 12:56.844
let loose at a buffet
at Mohegan Sun.

12:56.844 --> 12:57.945
- I like these jeans.

12:57.978 --> 12:59.079
They're comfortable!

12:59.112 --> 13:00.981
- All right.
Calm down.

13:01.014 --> 13:02.249
- No, I won't calm down.

13:02.282 --> 13:03.283
I am older than you.

13:03.316 --> 13:05.118
I am older than Lex.

13:05.152 --> 13:06.887
I'm older than my colleagues.

13:06.920 --> 13:09.923
Some people might even think
I'm older than my mother.

13:09.957 --> 13:10.924
I don't care.

13:10.958 --> 13:12.860
In fact, I am happier now

13:12.860 --> 13:14.862
than I was in my 20s
and my 30s.

13:14.862 --> 13:15.863
And you know what else?

13:15.863 --> 13:17.998
Brett Favre wears dad jeans.

13:18.031 --> 13:18.999
[phone ringing
"Bad to the Bone"]

13:19.032 --> 13:21.234
- Please take them off.

13:21.268 --> 13:23.370
Hi.

13:23.403 --> 13:25.438
- I think I just remembered
why I divorced Graham.

13:30.010 --> 13:30.878
- Now that Lex and I
are renewing our vows,

13:33.080 --> 13:35.215
we want to bring
some mystery and adventure

13:35.248 --> 13:36.483
into our marriage.

13:36.516 --> 13:38.285
- So we're eating dinner tonight

13:38.318 --> 13:39.887
in complete darkness.

13:39.920 --> 13:40.954
- Huh?
- What?

13:40.988 --> 13:41.922
- It's supposed to heighten

13:41.955 --> 13:42.956
all other senses.

13:42.990 --> 13:44.191
- Good for your palate

13:44.224 --> 13:46.894
and your libido, allegedly.
- Aww.

13:46.927 --> 13:48.228
- My senses were
already heightened

13:48.261 --> 13:49.796
when I heard we were eating
at 9:45.

13:49.897 --> 13:51.364
- Yeah, we're pretty tired too.

13:51.398 --> 13:53.800
Haven't been sleeping much
lately, if you know what I mean.

13:53.901 --> 13:55.468
- Yeah, we get it.
We get it.

13:55.502 --> 13:57.170
You're having lots of sex
'cause you're young.

13:57.204 --> 14:00.073
That's what young people do.
- Yeah.

14:00.107 --> 14:02.042
- Hello, and welcome
to Dinner in the Dark,

14:02.075 --> 14:03.810
a sensory adventure.

14:03.911 --> 14:05.545
We'll be putting on your masks
and lining you up

14:05.578 --> 14:07.915
as we review the dietary
restrictions you sent us.

14:07.948 --> 14:10.017
- Masks?
Seriously?

14:10.050 --> 14:12.319
No one asked us
our dietary restrictions.

14:12.352 --> 14:14.221
- Don't worry.
We got you covered.

14:14.254 --> 14:16.356
There's pretty much nothing
you guys don't eat, right?

14:16.389 --> 14:17.424
- Actually--
- Um.

14:17.457 --> 14:19.927
- Great.
Now, for Mrs. von Weber.

14:19.927 --> 14:22.829
No dairy, no gluten,
no meat, no oil,

14:22.930 --> 14:24.998
no vinegar, no starch,
no sugar.

14:25.032 --> 14:26.833
Is that everything?
- Sounds right.

14:26.934 --> 14:28.335
- And for Mr. von Weber.

14:28.368 --> 14:30.137
No soy, no bivalves,

14:30.170 --> 14:31.471
no grapefruit, no dill,

14:31.504 --> 14:34.607
no asparagus tips or bottoms--
just the middle--

14:34.641 --> 14:36.209
and American broccoli only.

14:36.243 --> 14:37.945
I assume that means
no Chinese broccoli

14:37.945 --> 14:39.346
or broccoli rabe?
- You got it.

14:39.379 --> 14:41.081
Lead me to my dinner.

14:41.114 --> 14:44.985
*

14:48.956 --> 14:51.959
- I am so, so sorry I'm late.

14:51.959 --> 14:56.163
You have no idea
the day I just had,

14:56.196 --> 14:58.098
but it doesn't matter.

15:01.268 --> 15:03.370
I should've called.
I should've texted.

15:03.403 --> 15:07.007
You can literally bite
my entire head off.

15:07.040 --> 15:08.441
I deserve it.

15:08.475 --> 15:10.443
- It's okay.

15:10.477 --> 15:11.544
- What?
Why are you smiling?

15:11.578 --> 15:12.645
It's freaking me out.

15:12.679 --> 15:14.414
- It's fine, really.

15:14.447 --> 15:15.415
Let's order.

15:15.448 --> 15:17.217
- No, it's not fine.

15:17.250 --> 15:20.187
What's going on?
Don't you want to bawl me out?

15:20.220 --> 15:22.622
- No, that's the beauty
of not being married anymore.

15:22.655 --> 15:25.558
I love the clarity
I have right now.

15:25.592 --> 15:27.995
- About what?
About my lateness?

15:27.995 --> 15:29.429
'Cause I know it's annoying,
but it's--

15:29.462 --> 15:31.999
it's not the reason
we got divorced.

15:31.999 --> 15:33.900
- Obviously, but...

15:34.001 --> 15:35.135
you know.

15:35.168 --> 15:36.403
You were always on time
for work,

15:36.436 --> 15:39.472
never missed a flight
or surgery.

15:39.506 --> 15:41.308
Then you'd come home,
and you couldn't manage

15:41.341 --> 15:44.277
to be on time to meet me.

15:44.311 --> 15:45.878
Just saying.

15:48.215 --> 15:50.850
- How about we get
a bottle of wine?

15:50.883 --> 15:51.851
Each.

15:51.884 --> 15:53.920
- I'm not in the mood.

15:54.021 --> 15:55.255
- Okay, I'm getting the feeling

15:55.288 --> 15:57.424
that you want to just
call it a night.

15:57.457 --> 15:58.925
- No.

15:59.026 --> 16:00.860
Actually, I think
I'm in the mood

16:01.028 --> 16:03.196
for a martini.

16:03.230 --> 16:04.431
Dirty.

16:06.033 --> 16:06.933
[tambourine rattling]

16:07.034 --> 16:08.168
- I'm sorry, did someone

16:08.201 --> 16:09.669
just take me to the Lilith Fair?

16:09.702 --> 16:11.338
[tambourine rattling]

16:11.371 --> 16:13.606
- We will engage all
of your senses this evening,

16:13.640 --> 16:15.042
not just with the food

16:15.075 --> 16:17.377
but also with your environment.
Enjoy.

16:17.410 --> 16:19.112
[all snap fingers]

16:19.146 --> 16:21.181
- No bread.

16:21.214 --> 16:22.449
- How did she know
there was bread?

16:22.482 --> 16:24.284
- I'd like to propose a toast

16:24.317 --> 16:25.685
to the love of my life,

16:25.718 --> 16:27.087
Brooke.
- Aww.

16:27.120 --> 16:29.656
- In your eyes,
the light, the heat.

16:29.689 --> 16:31.591
In your eyes, I am complete.

16:31.624 --> 16:33.260
Cheers.
- Cheers.

16:33.293 --> 16:34.627
- A little something I wrote...
- Wow.

16:34.661 --> 16:36.163
- Myself.
- Incredible.

16:36.196 --> 16:38.465
- Cheers.
- Beautiful, honey.

16:38.498 --> 16:40.467
- Here is your first course.

16:40.500 --> 16:41.934
Enjoy.

16:41.968 --> 16:42.935
- Mmm.

16:42.969 --> 16:44.071
It's warm.

16:44.071 --> 16:45.538
I would like to make
my own toast.

16:45.572 --> 16:48.275
- Oh, sorry, I have to
take out my Invisalign.

16:48.308 --> 16:49.609
Sorry, it's so gross.

16:49.642 --> 16:52.112
[muffled]
I usually do this in private,

16:52.145 --> 16:54.081
but you guys can't see me,
so who cares?

16:54.081 --> 16:55.348
Anyway, continue.

16:55.382 --> 16:57.550
- To Jill, who's been
so determined

16:57.584 --> 16:59.419
to jump-start her career.

16:59.452 --> 17:00.487
[egg shaker sounding]

17:00.520 --> 17:02.155
She even came to me--

17:02.189 --> 17:03.690
she was nervous,
I could tell--

17:03.723 --> 17:06.993
to ask if Von Weber
had any openings,

17:07.094 --> 17:10.097
and I imparted to her
my philosophy

17:10.130 --> 17:12.399
about not mixing
work and family.

17:12.432 --> 17:13.466
- I heard it the first time.

17:13.500 --> 17:15.268
- But as Joy Green would say--

17:15.302 --> 17:16.269
[triangle rings]

17:16.303 --> 17:17.537
"Every wise rule

17:17.570 --> 17:19.506
has an even wiser exception,"

17:19.539 --> 17:22.609
so I am offering you a job

17:22.642 --> 17:25.678
to oversee Von Weber's
Instagram account.

17:25.712 --> 17:27.214
- Oh, well, that--
honey, that's a--

17:27.247 --> 17:28.715
- What?
- Yeah.

17:28.748 --> 17:31.451
I want to help you
find your joy, Jill.

17:31.484 --> 17:35.122
I see you struggling,
and it pains me.

17:35.155 --> 17:38.325
- First of all, Brooke,
I'm not "struggling."

17:38.358 --> 17:40.227
I'm actually working
on a project right now

17:40.260 --> 17:41.461
that I'm very excited about.

17:41.494 --> 17:43.563
- This better not be
asparagus tip.

17:43.596 --> 17:45.165
- Yes, so I'm gonna have to

17:45.198 --> 17:48.135
respectfully decline
your generous offer.

17:48.168 --> 17:49.502
- Okay, well,

17:49.536 --> 17:51.304
I was just trying to help.

17:52.639 --> 17:54.141
I won't make that mistake again.

17:54.141 --> 17:55.442
- That's definitely
asparagus tip.

17:55.475 --> 17:56.509
Gross.

17:56.543 --> 17:58.711
- I just thought
it could be fun.

17:58.745 --> 18:00.247
- Really?

18:03.650 --> 18:05.352
Look, Brooke, the reason
that I'm passing

18:05.385 --> 18:06.719
is honestly because of you.

18:06.753 --> 18:08.355
- Yeah, I'm getting
that feeling

18:08.388 --> 18:09.522
loud and clear.
- No, no, no.

18:09.556 --> 18:10.523
That's not what I mean.

18:10.557 --> 18:12.425
I'm saying, you decided

18:12.459 --> 18:13.793
you were gonna be a designer,

18:13.826 --> 18:16.296
and then you did it,
and look at your company.

18:16.329 --> 18:17.397
It's exploded.

18:17.430 --> 18:19.399
- Yeah, I have had
a meteoric rise.

18:19.432 --> 18:22.169
- And I don't want to regret
taking the safe route.

18:22.169 --> 18:24.704
You never do,
and I admire that.

18:24.737 --> 18:27.807
- Please enjoy your next course.

18:31.378 --> 18:32.412
- [stammering]

18:32.445 --> 18:34.181
We're all set.
Thanks.

18:34.181 --> 18:35.715
- Jill, thank you.

18:35.748 --> 18:37.184
You're reminding me:

18:37.217 --> 18:39.186
I don't give myself
enough credit.

18:39.186 --> 18:40.853
- [exclaiming]

18:40.887 --> 18:42.522
I taste a little something
hairy in there.

18:42.555 --> 18:43.690
That--mm-mm.

18:43.723 --> 18:45.024
That's--I think that's dill.

18:45.057 --> 18:46.293
Was dill not on my list?

18:46.326 --> 18:47.594
Did the list just
go out the window?

18:47.627 --> 18:48.595
'Cause that was dill.

18:48.628 --> 18:49.596
[gags]

18:49.629 --> 18:50.697
- Whatever I'm eating,

18:50.730 --> 18:52.299
it's delicious.

18:52.332 --> 18:54.634
It's like a whole new
sensation in my mouth.

18:54.667 --> 18:56.203
What is this strange flavor

18:56.203 --> 18:57.604
and texture?
- [gagging]

18:57.637 --> 18:59.306
- Should we be doing
the Heimlich or something?

18:59.339 --> 19:01.341
- No, I'm pretty sure
if he can make a sound,

19:01.374 --> 19:02.475
he can breathe.

19:03.676 --> 19:04.644
Uh-oh.

19:04.677 --> 19:06.879
- Lex?
Lex?

19:06.913 --> 19:08.415
Lex.

19:08.448 --> 19:10.217
Okay, I'm taking my mask off.

19:10.217 --> 19:11.351
My brother has eaten dill.

19:11.384 --> 19:12.385
Turn the lights up, please.

19:12.419 --> 19:13.386
He's choking!

19:13.420 --> 19:15.355
- [choking]

19:15.388 --> 19:16.423
- Ready?

19:16.456 --> 19:17.890
- [grunts]
I'm fine!

19:17.924 --> 19:19.226
[clearing throat]
I'm good.

19:19.259 --> 19:20.827
- Was I just eating...

19:20.860 --> 19:22.262
bread crumbs?

19:24.464 --> 19:25.432
[vomiting]

19:25.465 --> 19:26.466
- Oh, my God.

19:29.569 --> 19:30.803
think
I lost my Invisalign.

19:30.837 --> 19:32.439
- Did you check the case?

19:32.472 --> 19:35.475
- Yes, and my purse,
and my pockets.

19:35.508 --> 19:36.643
Oh, my God, what if I--

19:36.676 --> 19:37.644
what if I ate it?

19:37.677 --> 19:39.145
There was a chewy course.

19:39.246 --> 19:40.880
There was a very chewy course.

19:40.913 --> 19:42.515
It was calamari, right?

19:42.549 --> 19:43.516
- I don't think so.

19:43.550 --> 19:44.584
- Oh, my God.

19:44.617 --> 19:46.619
I--I think I ate my Invisalign.

19:46.653 --> 19:48.255
I'm gonna kill myself!

19:48.255 --> 19:49.789
- Did you check your mouth?

19:51.924 --> 19:53.660
[both laughing]

19:53.693 --> 19:55.262
- Will you still love me

19:55.262 --> 19:56.863
if I only have a fraction
of my marbles?

19:56.896 --> 20:00.867
- I will love you even after
I have forgotten who you are.

20:00.900 --> 20:03.536
- Well, just for that,

20:03.570 --> 20:05.372
I'm taking 'em out again.
- Oh.

20:05.405 --> 20:07.674
- And you know what that means.

20:07.707 --> 20:09.576
- Va, va, voom.

20:09.609 --> 20:11.911
- But wait, there's more.

20:14.347 --> 20:15.982
- Well, I don't need more.

20:19.486 --> 20:22.655
[both sigh]

20:22.689 --> 20:25.658
- Man.
- I mean, really.

20:27.794 --> 20:29.228
Does that count
as break-up sex

20:29.262 --> 20:30.497
if it's eleven years late?

20:30.530 --> 20:33.433
- Sure, why not?

20:33.466 --> 20:35.134
- [gasps]

20:35.167 --> 20:37.604
917-555-0176.

20:37.637 --> 20:38.605
Yes!

20:38.638 --> 20:41.608
[upbeat rock music]

20:41.641 --> 20:43.343
*

20:43.376 --> 20:44.377
- What just happened?

20:44.411 --> 20:46.513
- Long story.
- Okay.

20:46.546 --> 20:48.681
- I'm not getting any younger.

20:49.782 --> 20:51.518
- Oh, hi, there.

20:51.551 --> 20:54.821
I wanted to introduce you
to my very sexy weighted vest

20:54.854 --> 20:57.624
to battle my geriatric bones.

20:57.657 --> 20:58.625
- Oho.

20:58.658 --> 21:00.226
- And you want to hear something

21:00.259 --> 21:01.828
that's really gonna turn you on?

21:01.861 --> 21:02.862
- Mm-hmm.

21:02.895 --> 21:05.765
- It's covered by insurance.

21:05.798 --> 21:07.667
- Now, that's hot.

21:07.700 --> 21:10.337
- And I have a present for you.

21:10.337 --> 21:12.772
- [laughing]

21:12.805 --> 21:14.006
Oh, God,

21:14.040 --> 21:15.675
you weigh a ton.

21:15.708 --> 21:18.244
- It's weight-bearing exercise
for both of us.

21:18.345 --> 21:21.814
- [laughing]

21:21.848 --> 21:24.817
- For more "Odd Mom Out,"
go to Bravotv.com.

21:24.851 --> 21:26.819
[seagulls calling]
- Oh, dear.
